    "Each neuron in a hidden layer applies an activation function to a weighted sum of its inputs, producing an output.",
    "Output Layer: The output layer typically consists of a single neuron for binary classification.",
    "The output neuron's activation function maps the weighted sum of inputs to a probability score between 0 and 1.",
    "The mathematical formulation of a single neuron in a hidden or output layer can be expressed as:",
    "• zi represents the weighted sum of inputs to neuron i."
